Crate root for `ctx-summarize`, the tool that walks a context tree bottom-up and regenerates `.ctx` leaf/aggregate summaries. This file is pure module wiring — no logic — and declares the layering contract other files in the crate must respect.

Layering (enforced by convention, not by the compiler): `cli` handles argv/IO only, calls into `runner`, which is pure orchestration logic sitting over two seams, `fs` and `agent`. Edits that add filesystem or LLM-calling code directly into `runner` violate this — such calls belong behind the `fs`/`agent` seams so `runner` stays testable without touching disk or a real agent.

Key invariant stated in the doc comment and binding on every module here: prompt text lives only in `prompts/` files loaded at runtime, never inlined as Rust string literals, and `intent.md` (used elsewhere in the ctx-tooling family) is deliberately never written by this tool. `cpath` presumably handles context-tree path logic and `progress` user-facing progress reporting, but neither is elaborated in this file — check their own leaf docs for specifics.